rsyslog server
allow syslog traffic through firewall
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=syslog
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

recieve messages on port 514

edit the /etc/rsyslog.conf file
uncomment the last 2 lines in the sectionjs starting with "provides udp/tcp syslog reception"
systemctl restart rsyslog

test using 
netstat -tupan : grep 514

rsyslog client
create file "/etc/rsyslog.d/filename.conf" containing one line
user.notice @syslogserverip

